---
title: Mexican Black Bean Bake with Buckwheat and Creme Fraiche
description: The star of tonight’s dish is ultra-nutritious, super-tasty buckwheat. It's misleadingly named since it's not wheat at all. It's not even a grain. In fact it's a seed and is related to rhubarb! It's popular in Japan in the form of soba noodles and the French turn it into savoury pancakes called 'galettes'. We love buckwheat's nutty flavour and today we'll be enjoying it in this Mexican-inspired bake.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/mexican-black-bean-bake-b8c9f583.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/mexican-black-bean-bake-4e494257.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/mexican-black-bean-bake-591f306199052d38ba162cd3
course: main course
cuisine: Mexican
time required: 35 minutes
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
